10 contrary to the determination of the treating provider and is based primarily
11 on cost-containment or utilization management criteria that conflict with
12 generally accepted standards of care.
13 B. For the purposes of this Section, "lower level of care" means any
14 healthcare service or setting that provides less intensive treatment, monitoring,
15 supervision, or therapeutic intervention than that recommended by the treating
16 provider.
