DIGEST
SB 363 Engrossed 2026 Regular Session Barrow
Proposed law prohibits an insurer from requiring an insured to accept a lower level of care
when it is contrary to the determination of the treating provider.
Proposed law provides an exception for an alternative level of care consistent with generally
accepted standards of medical practice.
Effective August 1, 2026.
(Adds R.S. 22:1128.1)
